{
  "texts": [
    "In recent years, there have been attempts to combine deep neural networks with IRT to improve prediction performance on responses (Cheng et al., 2019; Uto and Uchida, 2020; Tsutsumi et al., 2021; Zhou et al., 2021).",
    "The Deep Item Response Theory (Deep-IRT) model (Tsutsumi et al., 2021) has shown better response prediction performance than standard IRT models.",
    "However, IRT assumes that student and item parameters are static and do not account for student state changes.",
    "A number of emerging studies predicted students learning performance by estimating learning engagement and examining its relationship with student performance.",
    "Due to the affect-rich nature of facial expressions, emotion recognition methods have often been used for predicting learning engagement (Joshi et al., 2019; Abedi and Khan, 2021; Ruiz et al., 2021)."
  ]
}